{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, for fair comparison, backpropaga tion also updated weights 16 times on each batch of data.",
    "Training in each configuration (each learning rule and each learning rate) was repeated three times with different seeds.",
    "To extend a predictive coding network to a convolutional neural network (or to any network with a layered structure 58, 73), we can define the forward function of a layer (that is, how the input of layer l + 1 is computed from the neural activity of layer l) with weights w l to be ℱ w w w l (x x x l).",
    "For example, for the MLPs described above, ℱ w w w l (x x x l) = w w w l f (x x x l).",
    "For a convolutional network, ℱ w w w l (x x x l) is a more complex function of w l and x l, and also w l and x l are not simple matrix and vector anymore (to be defined later)."
  ]
}